description: The aisles of this store are packed with packaged snacks and drinks, marked at considerably higher prices than similar items elsewhere. Much of the store is dedicated to newspapers and other reading material for long flights.

description: This building is five stories tall and made of aged brick. It has several wings that are asymmetrical to one another and appear to have been constructed at different times. A large concrete staircase ascends to a grand, stone-arched entrance set into what appears to be the oldest part of the building.
name: Northern Dorms

description: Despite the building's aged exterior, the interior has clearly been recently renovated, and the lights, paint and fixtures are all very new. The dorm rooms themselves are very small and cluttered, but are nevertheless comfortable and surprisingly well-lit.
name: Northern Dorms

description: The interior art studios are filled with easels, still-life props and half-finished student artwork. The studios on the top floor are cluttered with architectural drawings and building models that appear to have been printed out of a clear plastic resin.
name: Art & Music

description: This is an imposing building built of red brick. This wing of the library contains most of the university archives, and the facade has been renovated recently. Sheets of paper swirl down the street in the wind.
name: E. Tobias Hawking Library

description: Several tables and chairs are placed about the place and there is a large kitchen in the back. Several large televisions hang from the walls, which are decorated with jerseys and photographs of various sporting feats accomplished by Cimmerian University student athletes.
name: MegaBites

description: This area is dominated by the trunks of tall evergreen trees. The undergrowth is damp and thick with moss and ferns. A small, solitary grave marker juts out of the ground on the edge of the forest, near the pond. The words on its surface have been eroded away over time.
name: Cimmerian Forest

description: This area is filled with tall grass that flows and whispers in the breeze. It is crisscrossed with recreation trails for walking and bicycling, as well as the occasional bench or picnic table. A building once stood here, but all that is left is its stone foundation, now covered in moss.
name: Cimmerian Field

description: This building is five stories tall and made of aged brick that is almost entirely overrun with vines and ivy. Colorful athletic pennants hang in many of the cast iron windows.
name: Northern Dorms

description: The hallways and stairwells of this building are narrow and the carpets and paint are fading, but the doors and security systems appear to be state-of-the-art. The ceilings in the dorm rooms themselves are very high, and some contain impromptu lofts that the residents had built for themselves.

name: Cimmeria History Museum

name: Cimmeria History Museum

description: This building appears to be a farmhouse of some kind. It has been extensively remodelled over the years but still resembles its original state. In front of the farmhouse is a small, faded plaque detailing the history of the land now occupied by Cimmerian University.
name: Lucien's Farmhouse

description: This building was once a home, but when the university was established it was converted into a historical site. There are a few old furnishings here, though perhaps not as old as the house. The walls have modern electrical outlets.
name: Lucien's Farmhouse

description: This is a small ferry terminal intended for use by the city's high speed ferries. There are numerous papers and some discarded suitcases lying about.
name: Silver City Ferry Terminal

description: The building is about two dozen stories tall and is made of glass and steel. Its facade shimmers in the light, though none of its offices show signs of occupation from the outside. A small enclosed shelter for a bus stop can be found here.
name: Resistor Systems

description: A clean, simple lobby area leads to higher floors, which are filled with empty, cobweb ridden cubicles. The elevators no longer work, and the stairwells are littered with papers.
name: Resistor Systems

description: This building is a three-story cylinder clad in tinted structural glass and emblazoned with a large, simple corporate logo. It is set in the center of a tree-lined plaza paved in pristine white slate.
name: Paragon Store

description: The ground level is a spacious sales floor in which the latest trends in bionic augmentations are on display, while the upper floors contain state-of-the-art surgical suites for installing and upgrading augmentations. The decor makes use of organic forms, high-quality materials and a minimum of color.
name: Paragon Store

description: The cages and and exhibits here are empty, and bits of trash - handbills, mostly - blow in the wind. A brightly painted antique carousel stands here. The machinery that operated it is broken, but faint music-box sounds can be heard as the wind blows through it.
name: Laurentia City Zoo

description: The cages and and exhibits here are empty, and bits of trash - handbills, mostly - blow in the wind. A large concrete habitat that once housed great apes can be found here, but it sits empty and still save for an idle water feature and rope swings that sway in the breeze.
name: Laurentia City Zoo

description: This quaint-looking bar is made of wood and plaster, and looks rather faded. The sign above the door is peeling, though one can still make out the name of the bar painted in gold above a coat of arms, with a huge bite taken out of it. On the shield, quartered bats and wolves seem to be dancing around the tooth marks.
name: The Winchester

description: This old-timey tavern is full of wooden furniture stained a rich umber. The bartop is clawed to pieces, and there seem to be broken bottles nearly carpeting the floor. Despite that, the bar is quite cozy, and there is a neatly-organized mountain of liquor behind the bar.
name: The Winchester

description: This is a small ferry terminal intended for use by the city's high speed ferries. Families often used this terminal, and toys are scattered about.
name: Wolverton Ferry Terminal

description: The building is several stories tall and is made of glass and steel. A news ticker on the outside of the building's main entrance is dark and non-functional.
name: Laurentia Stock Exchange

description: This building is comprised of a huge trading floor, cordoned off but kept in pristine condition. Massive displays along the walls, presumably meant to display stock information, are non-functional.
name: Laurentia Stock Exchange

description: This enormous, imposing building, by far the tallest in the city, is over a hundred stories tall. The tower dwarfs everything nearby, and the top is dominated by a large glassed-in aperture that spans the width of the building. The tower reflects enough light that it appears to glow slightly at all hours of the day.
name: Olympic Tower

description: This is the tower's lobby. Numerous electronic security checkpoints, now deactivated and unmanned, sit idle. They serve as barriers between the main lobby area and the elevators, none of which function. No stairwells are visible. An ornate fresco, depicting a divine struggle between good and evil, decorates the walls and ceiling.
name: Olympic Tower

description: This is a posh establishment meant to resemble a nightclub from about a century ago, with the lighting and furniture all appropriately antique. A stage off in the corner has banners alongside it, advertising a forthcoming jazz concert that never ended up happening.

description: The facade of this imposing building is made of soaring granite columns with intricately carved capitals. A grand stair leads up from the street to the main entrance. A ramp has been added more recently, though it does a good job of blending in with the original finish of the building.
name: Bank of Laurentia

description: The main room of this building is very large, with soaring, vaulted ceilings. Many antique desks with modern lighting fixtures are arranged throughout the area. Monumental stairs with elegant ironwork lead up to several floors of offices and down to the vaults.
name: Bank of Laurentia

description: This ten-story structure consists of a jumble of interconnected buildings made of grey concrete panels, though all appear to have been built at the same time. Signs directing visitors to the emergency room and other departments are the most colorful sights present.
name: Connolly General Hospital

description: The interior of the hospital is difficult to navigate and consists of several wings, some of which have clearly been renovated more recently than others. The air is stale and smells of harsh hand cleaning agents. A faint beeping noise can sometimes be heard, but no source of the sound is evident.
name: Connolly General Hospital

description: This is a large glass building that stands about fifteen stories tall. It has a luxurious appearance and bright red signage on the top of the building.
name: Park Royale

description: An extravagant lobby and bar area at the entrance gives way to stairwells and elevators here, both leading to rooms which are luxurious but for the most part, identical. You find yourself easily lost in the winding, identical corridors.
name: Park Royale

description: This building is made of glass and terracotta, with a curved facade that wraps around a large central atrium. It is surrounded by a brick-paved plaza lined with well-tended trees and wrought-iron streetlamps.
name: Wolverton Public Library

description: The walls inside the tower are made of a pristine, white marble. There are bright, polished machines composed of gears and bits of clockwork everywhere throughout the building, each rotating in unison for some unknown purpose.

The doors to to this large building appear to be made of intricately carved marble. Dominating the front of the building is a large statue of a woman with her arms outstretched in a welcoming gesture. The entire area exudes an aura of peace and tranquility.
name: Mount Kunlun

description: The inside of this building consists of a single large room. Spread about the area are several beds made of marble that appear surprisingly comfortable despite the material used in their construction. Lining one wall are several cabinets and chests, and a large firepit is centered in the room.
name: Mount Kunlun

description: This is a towering structure with a glistening sheen, although it was obviously constructed in the distant past. Several imposing statues, all of which seem to be angelic heroes, stand at attention on the ramparts.

description: This is a rounded tower of whitewashed brick that stands atop a rocky promontory overlooking the sea. It is connected to a simple clapboard house that once housed lighthouse keepers. The lamp is dark.
name: Hall of the Gatekeeper

description: The keeper's quarters are clean, if small, and have been preserved to reflect living conditions roughly a century ago. The lantern chamber atop the tower contains a huge, elaborate lens made of many pieces of curved glass.
name: Hall of the Gatekeeper

description: This windowless whitewashed building is in a state of mild disrepair. An iron gate swings on rusted hinges in front of the door and the grass around the building has grown wild and long.
You are standing inside a small, white-walled building filled with dust and cobwebs. Several moldering bodies are laid in the niches on either side of the room. The faint reek of death is everywhere.

The ground here is covered in a hard, icy snow, muddied and marred by inhuman footprints and splotches of blood and bile. The temperature is well below freezing. Out of the corner of your eye you seem to catch glimpses of naked wretches, shivering and blue, but when you look directly at them they disappear. The wind shrieks and howls about you.
name: River Phlegethon

This small room is spartan, nearly austere in its simplicity.  The floor is covered with mats made of woven rushes, giving visitors a comfortable place to sit.  A piece of decorative scrollwork hangs in a recessed alcove, where also stands a thrown pottery vase with a single flower in it.
